{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VfzpFHG5uibyhwPGs1pzaC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { useState } from \"react\";\n     2→import type { Tier } from \"@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser\";\n     3→import type { UIMatch } from \"../types\";\n     4→import { MatchCard } from \"./MatchCard\";\n     5→\n     6→type SortOption = \"newest\" | \"oldest\" | \"amount\";\n     7→\n     8→interface OpenMatchesListProps {\n     9→  matches: UIMatch[];\n    10→  loading: boolean;\n    11→  onJoin: (matchId: string) => void;\n    12→  joiningMatchId: string | null;\n    13→  currentUserAddress: string | null;\n    14→  selectedTier: Tier | null;\n    15→  isConnected: boolean;\n    16→}\n    17→\n    18→function sortMatches(matches: UIMatch[], sort: SortOption): UIMatch[] {\n    19→  return [...matches].sort((a, b) => {\n    20→    switch (sort) {\n    21→      case \"newest\":\n    22→        return b.createdAt - a.createdAt;\n    23→      case \"oldest\":\n    24→        return a.createdAt - b.createdAt;\n    25→      case \"amount\":\n    26→        return b.entryAmount - a.entryAmount;\n    27→    }\n    28→  });\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→export function OpenMatchesList({\n    32→  matches,\n    33→  loading,\n    34→  onJoin,\n    35→  joiningMatchId,\n    36→  currentUserAddress,\n    37→  selectedTier,\n    38→  isConnected,\n    39→}: OpenMatchesListProps) {\n    40→  const [sortBy, setSortBy] = useState<SortOption>(\"newest\");\n    41→\n    42→  // Filter by tier if selected\n    43→  const filteredMatches = selectedTier\n    44→    ? matches.filter((m) => m.tier === selectedTier)\n    45→    : matches;\n    46→\n    47→  // Apply sort\n    48→  const sortedMatches = sortMatches(filteredMatches, sortBy);\n    49→\n    50→  if (loading) {\n    51→    return (\n    52→      <div className=\"coinflip-matches coinflip-matches--loading\">\n    53→        <div className=\"coinflip-matches__spinner\" />\n    54→        <p>Loading games...</p>\n    55→      </div>\n    56→    );\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  if (sortedMatches.length === 0) {\n    60→    return (\n    61→      <div className=\"coinflip-matches coinflip-matches--empty\">\n    62→        <p className=\"coinflip-matches__empty-text\">\n    63→          {selectedTier\n    64→            ? `No open ${selectedTier} games`\n    65→            : \"No open games available\"}\n    66→        </p>\n    67→        <p className=\"coinflip-matches__empty-hint\">\n    68→          Create a game or wait for someone to create one\n    69→        </p>\n    70→      </div>\n    71→    );\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  return (\n    75→    <div className=\"coinflip-matches\">\n    76→      <div className=\"coinflip-matches__header\">\n    77→        <h3 className=\"coinflip-matches__title\">Open Games</h3>\n    78→        <div className=\"coinflip-matches__controls\">\n    79→          <select\n    80→            className=\"coinflip-matches__sort\"\n    81→            value={sortBy}\n    82→            onChange={(e) => setSortBy(e.target.value as SortOption)}\n    83→          >\n    84→            <option value=\"newest\">Newest</option>\n    85→            <option value=\"oldest\">Oldest</option>\n    86→            <option value=\"amount\">Amount</option>\n    87→          </select>\n    88→          <span className=\"coinflip-matches__count\">\n    89→            {sortedMatches.length} available\n    90→          </span>\n    91→        </div>\n    92→      </div>\n    93→\n    94→      <div className=\"coinflip-matches__list\">\n    95→        {sortedMatches.map((match) => {\n    96→          const isOwn = currentUserAddress === match.player1;\n    97→          const canJoin = isConnected && !isOwn;\n    98→\n    99→          return (\n   100→            <MatchCard\n   101→              key={match.id}\n   102→              match={match}\n   103→              onJoin={() => onJoin(match.id)}\n   104→              isOwn={isOwn}\n   105→              canJoin={canJoin}\n   106→              joining={joiningMatchId === match.id}\n   107→            />\n   108→          );\n   109→        })}\n   110→      </div>\n   111→    </div>\n   112→  );\n   113→}\n   114→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"73651d8d-ca1a-4f9e-b9b7-f2b958b23ec2","uuid":"90b604bd-8ea0-4d24-b2fc-9a884859a335","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/OpenMatchesList.tsx","content":"import { useState } from \"react\";\nimport type { Tier } from \"@rng-utopia/game-engine/browser\";\nimport type { UIMatch } from \"../types\";\nimport { MatchCard } from \"./MatchCard\";\n\ntype SortOption = \"newest\" | \"oldest\" | \"amount\";\n\ninterface OpenMatchesListProps {\n  matches: UIMatch[];\n  loading: boolean;\n  onJoin: (matchId: string) => void;\n  joiningMatchId: string | null;\n  currentUserAddress: string | null;\n  selectedTier: Tier | null;\n  isConnected: boolean;\n}\n\nfunction sortMatches(matches: UIMatch[], sort: SortOption): UIMatch[] {\n  return [...matches].sort((a, b) => {\n    switch (sort) {\n      case \"newest\":\n        return b.createdAt - a.createdAt;\n      case \"oldest\":\n        return a.createdAt - b.createdAt;\n      case \"amount\":\n        return b.entryAmount - a.entryAmount;\n    }\n  });\n}\n\nexport function OpenMatchesList({\n  matches,\n  loading,\n  onJoin,\n  joiningMatchId,\n  currentUserAddress,\n  selectedTier,\n  isConnected,\n}: OpenMatchesListProps) {\n  const [sortBy, setSortBy] = useState<SortOption>(\"newest\");\n\n  // Filter by tier if selected\n  const filteredMatches = selectedTier\n    ? matches.filter((m) => m.tier === selectedTier)\n    : matches;\n\n  // Apply sort\n  const sortedMatches = sortMatches(filteredMatches, sortBy);\n\n  if (loading) {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"coinflip-matches coinflip-matches--loading\">\n        <div className=\"coinflip-matches__spinner\" />\n        <p>Loading games...</p>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n\n  if (sortedMatches.length === 0) {\n    return (\n      <div className=\"coinflip-matches coinflip-matches--empty\">\n        <p className=\"coinflip-matches__empty-text\">\n          {selectedTier\n            ? `No open ${selectedTier} games`\n            : \"No open games available\"}\n        </p>\n        <p className=\"coinflip-matches__empty-hint\">\n          Create a game or wait for someone to create one\n        </p>\n      </div>\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"coinflip-matches\">\n      <div className=\"coinflip-matches__header\">\n        <h3 className=\"coinflip-matches__title\">Open Games</h3>\n        <div className=\"coinflip-matches__controls\">\n          <select\n            className=\"coinflip-matches__sort\"\n            value={sortBy}\n            onChange={(e) => setSortBy(e.target.value as SortOption)}\n          >\n            <option value=\"newest\">Newest</option>\n            <option value=\"oldest\">Oldest</option>\n            <option value=\"amount\">Amount</option>\n          </select>\n          <span className=\"coinflip-matches__count\">\n            {sortedMatches.length} available\n          </span>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div className=\"coinflip-matches__list\">\n        {sortedMatches.map((match) => {\n          const isOwn = currentUserAddress === match.player1;\n          const canJoin = isConnected && !isOwn;\n\n          return (\n            <MatchCard\n              key={match.id}\n              match={match}\n              onJoin={() => onJoin(match.id)}\n              isOwn={isOwn}\n              canJoin={canJoin}\n              joining={joiningMatchId === match.id}\n            />\n          );\n        })}\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n","numLines":114,"startLine":1,"totalLines":114}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015ZeFAwyNne7otWP8mhyuBv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear understanding of what needs to be done. Let me implement:\n\n1. **CoinflipContext.tsx**: \n   - Import `fetchClaimableMatches` from chain.ts\n   - Add `claimableMatches: UIMatch[]` to state\n   - Add `claimableMatches` to context value type and value\n   - Poll `fetchClaimableMatches` alongside open matches in `refreshMatches` (when publicKey is available)\n\n2. **CoinflipPage.tsx**:\n   - Destructure `claimableMatches` from `useCoinflip()`\n   - Show a \"Your Matches\" section above the lobby list with claim/cancel per match\n\nNow I'm implementing these changes. The context needs to fetch claimable matches only when the wallet is connected, and the UI should display a dedicated section for user matches with action buttons that vary based on each match's current phase.\n\nThe tricky part is that `refreshMatches` doesn't directly access `publicKey`, so I need to restructure it to fetch claimable matches whenever the public key becomes available, whether during initial load or polling. modify it or add a separate fetch alongside it.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to make the claimable matches fetching happen in the same polling effect, similar to how open matches are polled. Or I could include it in `refreshMatches`.\n\nLooking at the current code, I could modify this to also fetch claimable matches when publicKey is available. But `publicKey` changes, and I don't want to invalidate the callback too much. Actually, it's fine to add publicKey to the deps since it changes when wallet connects/disconnects.\n\nNow I'm implementing this by adding claimable matches state and modifying the refresh function to fetch both open and claimable matches in parallel, with the claimable fetch only running when a wallet is connected.\n\nFor the \"Your Matches\" section, I need to determine which action button to show based on the match phase: \"Cancel\" for matches the user created that are still waiting, \"Timeout Cancel\" for locked matches that have expired, and \"Claim\"/\"Settle\" for completed matches ready for payout.\n\nSince the main use cases are claiming resolved matches and canceling pending ones, I'll keep the UI straightforward and render the match cards directly in CoinflipPage above the open lobby list rather than creating a separate component.\n\nNow I'm realizing there's a tension with how claiming works — the `claimPayout` action requires `activeMatch` to be set, but users might want to claim a match without opening the full ActiveMatchView. I could either set the match as active when they click claim, or refactor the action to work without requiring `activeMatch` to be pre-set. I need to decide between adding inline action buttons directly in the \"Your Matches\" list versus routing through the existing ActiveMatchView. The spec calls for per-match actions in the list itself, so I'll add inline claim and cancel buttons that work with individual matches without requiring them to be set as active first. I'm going in circles here—the simplest approach is to add direct `claimSpecificMatch` and `cancelSpecificMatch` functions so each match card in the list can have its own action buttons without needing to navigate through ActiveMatchView first. Adding context methods for direct claim and cancel operations... use the existing flow, or I can have the cancel button work directly since `buildCancelMatchTx` just needs the creator pubkey.\n\nActually, for cancel: `cancelMatch` currently checks `activeMatch` exists. I could modify it OR add a new function. The simplest: when clicking cancel on a your-matches item, first set it as activeMatch, then the sidebar shows cancel button. But that changes the UI.\n\nLet me just add two new context methods:\n- `claimMatch(match: UIMatch): Promise<void>` - for claiming a specific match\n- `cancelSpecificMatch(match: UIMatch): Promise<void>` - for canceling a specific match\n\nWait, actually, let me look at this from another angle. The \"Your Matches\" section is for matches the user is involved in. When they click a match there:\n- If it's their waiting match → they want to cancel it\n- If it's a completed match → they want to claim/settle\n\nThe simplest approach is to add a `claimMatch` method to the context for direct claiming, while letting users click a match in \"Your Matches\" to view it in the ActiveMatchView where the existing cancel button works. The spec just needs a \"Your Matches\" section with claim and cancel actions available per match. match has claim/cancel buttons\n\nLet me implement it directly:\n- New UI section in CoinflipPage\n- Each match row: show tier, amount, phase, and action button(s)\n- Clicking the action button either claims or cancels\n\nFor the actions, I'll modify the context to expose these functions. Or better yet, I'll just set the match as activeMatch and let the existing UI handle it. The spec says \"actions per match\" but clicking to view + claim is an action.\n\nYou know what, let me just add a simple click handler that sets the match as activeMatch. That's the minimum needed. The ActiveMatchView already has all the claim/cancel buttons. The \"Your Matches\" section shows the matches with a \"View\" button or makes them clickable.\n\nBut to truly have \"claim/cancel actions per match\" inline, I need buttons. Let me compromise: each match card displays a phase indicator and contextual action buttons—\"Claim\" for completed matches, \"Cancel\" for created ones, and \"View\" for ready matches. Clicking any action sets the match as active and triggers the corresponding operation.\n\nActually, the most practical approach is to make the entire match card clickable to open it in ActiveMatchView, then add a quick \"Claim\" button for completed matches that directly sends the claim transaction without needing to navigate.\n\nFor the context, I need to import the claimable matches function, add state to track them, and fetch them whenever the public key is available during the refresh cycle. is available\n4. Add `claimableMatches` to context type and value\n5. Add `setActiveMatchFromClaimable(match: UIMatch)` or just expose a way to set activeMatch\n\nWait, there's already `setActiveMatch` state setter, but it's not exposed through context. The `clearActiveMatch` is exposed. I could add a `selectMatch` action that sets it as active.\n\nLet me check if there's a simpler approach. If I add inline action buttons that:\n1. For complete matches: set activeMatch + call claimPayout (but claimPayout reads from activeMatch which was JUST set — React state is batched, so it won't be available immediately)\n\nHmm, that's the issue. If I call `setActiveMatch(match)` and then `claimPayout()`, the `claimPayout` callback still sees the old activeMatch due to React's batching.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to add a `claimMatch(match: UIMatch)` function that takes the match directly, bypassing the activeMatch dependency, while also exposing `selectMatch` to let users view a match in the detail view. I'll keep it minimal and just add `claimableMatches` to the context, then wire up click handlers on the match cards to set activeMatch and display the ActiveMatchView. For convenience, add \"Claim\"/\"Cancel\" label on the card to indicate the action. The user clicks a match, sees it in ActiveMatchView, and uses the existing buttons.\n\nBut I need to expose `setActiveMatch` from the context — I could add a `selectMatch` method that sets the active match and clears the dismissed ref. Actually, re-reading the spec, it wants action buttons directly on each match card, so I should add a `claimMatch` function that works independently of the activeMatch state.\n\nMy plan is to update CoinflipContext to import the claimable matches fetcher, add state for tracking them, and refresh that list whenever the public key changes